{"lemma":"غابِر","slug":"غابِر","root":"غ.ب.ر","root_slug":"غ-ب-ر","root_link":"/words/roots/غ-ب-ر","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"غابِر","root":"غبر","pos":"N","occurrence_count":7},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["adj"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":2},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n31355"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%BA%D8%A7%D8%A8%D9%90%D8%B1"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"adj","gloss":"remaining"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"bygone, elapsed, past, antiquated"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Derived from the active participle of غَبَرَ (ḡabara, “to stay”)."},"ipa":["/ɣaː.bir/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n31355","headword_ar":"غَابِرٌ","root":"gbr","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Remaining; lasting; continuing:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Az, S, IAmb, Mgh:) this is the sense in which it is used by the Arabs: (Az:) or it is the meaning most commonly obtaining among them: (IAmb:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tarrying; staying; waiting:"},{"kind":"text","text":"pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gub~arN","text_ar":"غُبَّرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (K:) and the pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gaAbirapN","text_ar":"غَابِرَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gawaAbiru","text_ar":"غَوَابِرُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) You say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qawomN gub~arN","text_ar":"قَوْمٌ غُبَّرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A people remaining,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.]. (TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"guy~aru Aln~aAsi","text_ar":"غُيَّرُ النَّاسِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The later of mankind."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"huwa gaAbiru baniY","text_ar":"هُوَ غَابِرُ بَنِى"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fulaAnK","text_ar":"فُلَانٍ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He is the relic of the sons of such a one."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlgaAbiru mina All~ayoli","text_ar":"الغَابِرُ مِنَ اللَّيْلِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"What remains of the night."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jawofu All~ayoli AlgaAbiru","text_ar":"جَوْفُ اللَّيْلِ الغَابِرُ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The last division of the night."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlEa$oru AlgawaAbiru","text_ar":"العَشْرُ الغَوَابِرُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mino $ahori ramaDaAna","text_ar":"مِنْ شَهْرِ رَمَضَانَ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The remaining,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"last, ten"},{"kind":"text","text":"nights"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the month of Ramadán."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaTaEa","text_ar":"قَطَعَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A@ll~`hu gaAbirahu wadaAbirahu","text_ar":"ا@للّٰهُ غَابِرَهُ وَدَابِرَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"May God cut off the last, and what remains, of him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"may God extirpate him"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.) See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"guborN","text_ar":"غُبْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"-A2-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Passing; passing away; going away: past:"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maADK","text_ar":"مَاضٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (Az, S, IAmb, Mgh;) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*aAhibN","text_ar":"ذَاهِبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (K:) so accord. to some of the lexicologists: (Az:) or so used sometimes, as, for instance, by the poet El-Aashà: (IAmb:) thus it bears two contr. significations. (S.) You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^anota gaAbirN gadFAwa*ikoruka gaAbirN A^abadFA","text_ar":"اَنْتَ غَابِرٌ غَدًاوَذِكْرُكَ غَابِرٌ اَبَدًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Thou passest away to-morrow, but thy fame remaineth for ever"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.)       -A3-  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Future"},{"kind":"text","text":"time. See an ex. in the first of the verses cited voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hayovu","text_ar":"حَيْثُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". The meaning of “ remaining ” seems equally appropriate in that verse: but"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gAbr","text_ar":"غابر"},{"kind":"text","text":"is often used by grammarians in the last of the senses expl. above.]"}],"source_refs":["Az","S","IAmb","Mgh","K"]}]}}